anything of substance.

49
00:03:03,391 --> 00:03:11,135
One thing about academia is you definitely shouldn't think of it as just a stepping stone in your career.

50
00:03:11,155 --> 00:03:17,058
You should think of it as, if you're going to commit to it, really commit as a really important part of your career.

51
00:03:17,398 --> 00:03:19,640
And get the most out of it as you can.

52
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:26,844
If I just went to school and took my classes, I wouldn't have tried to go above and beyond and do cool shit.

53
00:03:28,318 --> 00:03:29,699
No to bad stock photos.

54
00:03:30,760 --> 00:03:33,541
So yeah, some benefits of academia are

55
00:03:33,841 --> 00:03:36,142
you'll learn really cool critical thinking skills

56
00:03:37,342 --> 00:03:39,723
that kind of help you think in a different way

57
00:03:39,763 --> 00:03:41,364
than just industry.

58
00:03:41,424 --> 00:03:43,485
I approach problems kind of differently maybe.

59
00:03:45,366 --> 00:03:48,087
And you can really push the boundaries of our medium.

60
00:03:48,607 --> 00:03:50,368
And you'll also end up with

61
