I've heard from a lot of grad students that they feel siloed from the rest of the industry,

66
00:04:08,497 --> 00:04:14,040
kind of over here in this weird corner. Your findings, although they will be cherished by

67
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:19,963
academia, they may not make it into the industry at large for a while, because the industry has...

68
00:04:21,144 --> 00:04:25,586
Well, I'll get to that. Next is industry.

69
00:04:26,588 --> 00:04:31,130
So you're kind of just thrown right into the deep end of the pool on this one.

70
00:04:31,150 --> 00:04:37,293
I just got to Hangar 13 and they threw the engine at me and they were like,

71
00:04:37,734 --> 00:04:41,956
all right, learn our scripting shit and you can do it. All right, go.

72
00:04:42,556 --> 00:04:46,418
So this is self-guided in kind of a different way.

73
00:04:46,878 --> 00:04:49,860
So you kind of have to be confident in, and even if you...

74
00:04:50,960 --> 00:04:55,462
aren't completely confident at the beginning, just know that you can

75
00:04:55,823 --> 00:04:58,764
eventually get it and just try.

76
00:04:58,784 --> 00:05:05,487
I couldn't find a stock but a diverse group of people working, I wonder why.

77
00:05:05,967 --> 00:05:13,711
But it's great for learning how to work in a really diverse, big group,

78
00:05:14,751 --> 00:05:15,232
potentially.

79
00:05:16,896 --> 00:05:20,058
The industry is extremely fast-paced, as you might have heard.

80
00:05:20,878 --> 00:05:22,458
You work under a lot of pressure.

81
00:05:23,719 --> 00:05:28,341
You have like deadlines, like academia has deadlines, but like industry has deadlines

82
00:05:28,381 --> 00:05:33,243
that are based on, you know, money and other people's jobs and like really high stakes.

83
00:05:34,610 --> 00:05:36,891
And in industry, there's less experimentation.

84
00:05:37,671 --> 00:05:39,312
Sometimes I'll try to propose something

85
00:05:39,352 --> 00:05:40,612
that I think is really cool,

86
00:05:41,292 --> 00:05:44,134
but it's always, can you prove it out?

87
00:05:45,214 --> 00:05:46,655
Even if it's a new concept,

88
00:05:46,735 --> 00:05:49,236
is it kind of rooted in a solid foundation

89
00:05:49,356 --> 00:05:52,777
that we know it'll succeed and do well and make us money?

90
00:05:53,517 --> 00:05:57,959
So for industry, it's cool to just kind of see,

91
00:05:58,359 --> 00:06:00,160
and really get down and dirty into the,

92
00:06:02,711 --> 00:06:05,693
actual work, I don't know. I mean, academia is actual work too, but anyway.

93
00:06:06,234 --> 00:06:11,618
And then you can work on really big projects and learn a lot of new tools and stuff.

94
00:06:12,838 --> 00:06:19,023
The downsides are that it can be a bit unforgiving. This is going to ring in a second.

95
00:06:21,425 --> 00:06:23,426
So yeah, you kind of just have to...

96
00:06:28,667 --> 00:06:34,532
But yeah, and you kind of just have to really throw yourself into it.

97
00:06:34,753 --> 00:06:38,376
And you can't really make too many mistakes.

98
00:06:38,996 --> 00:06:41,479
Well, you can, but only within reason.

99
00:06:41,499 --> 00:06:45,222
Like, academia, you can really explore who you are as a designer

100
00:06:45,282 --> 00:06:46,783
and what you want to do.

101
00:06:46,863 --> 00:06:51,347
And school is for making mistakes, but industry, it's less so.

102
00:06:51,367 --> 00:06:53,789
And morale, you know, whatever.

103
00:06:53,829 --> 00:06:55,371
It kind of depends on personality type.

104
00:06:56,010 --> 00:06:57,530
So which is for you?

105
00:06:58,971 --> 00:07:01,512
Depends on, you know, kind of just what you want to do

106
00:07:01,592 --> 00:07:03,873
and based on kind of both of these analyses,

107
00:07:03,933 --> 00:07:06,834
like what fits your personality, your goals,

108
00:07:07,114 --> 00:07:08,595
and the trajectory of your career.

109
00:07:09,375 --> 00:07:11,496
And you can always merge the two if you want.

110
00:07:11,596 --> 00:07:13,217
Like I did, you know, you can...

111
00:07:14,457 --> 00:07:16,218
Do academia first, then do industry.

112
00:07:16,298 --> 00:07:17,899
They both inform each other.

113
00:07:17,919 --> 00:07:20,700
They're not as divorced as you would think.

114
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:23,361
So that's always something you can do.

115
00:07:24,502 --> 00:07:27,103
And shoot for the stars, because you're awesome.

116
00:07:27,183 --> 00:07:27,603
Thanks.

117
00:07:28,223 --> 00:07:37,387
I think it's movie.

118
00:07:37,448 --> 00:07:37,628
Yeah.

119
00:07:37,728 --> 00:07:40,909
Awesome.

