00:27:21,792 --> 00:27:24,496
You can go to Toastmasters and you can practice ahead of time

514
00:27:24,836 --> 00:27:26,218
when the stakes aren't quite so high,

515
00:27:26,658 --> 00:27:28,480
so that it's more comfortable and more familiar

516
00:27:28,701 --> 00:27:30,082
when you finally have the opportunity.

517
00:27:31,346 --> 00:27:36,471
There's a saying, give a man a fish and you feed him for a day, teach a man a fish and

518
00:27:36,511 --> 00:27:37,512
you feed him for a lifetime.

519
00:27:38,273 --> 00:27:40,275
And I think that's kind of true across the board.

520
00:27:40,775 --> 00:27:46,761
If you say yes to everything, every single time, you become the go-to person for something,

521
00:27:46,861 --> 00:27:47,742
which is great for a while.

522
00:27:48,242 --> 00:27:53,284
but you also become somebody that is just doing the same thing over and over and over again.

523
00:27:53,744 --> 00:27:56,924
So in order to broaden your horizons and free up your time,

524
00:27:57,565 --> 00:28:00,245
make sure that you teach other people how to do things as well.

525
00:28:00,825 --> 00:28:04,566
So, great, I'm going to have this new opportunity, if it turns out I'm doing it all the time,

526
00:28:05,367 --> 00:28:08,527
I'm going to go and now teach you how to do it so that every time you ask me,

527
00:28:08,547 --> 00:28:09,868
I don't have to bother.

528
00:28:10,188 --> 00:28:12,388
Some of this is because I'm a programmer and I just like to automate things,

529
00:28:12,648 --> 00:28:14,689
but, you know, that's just how it kind of goes.

530
00:28:15,998 --> 00:28:18,699
