I need to have a really low ping,

534
00:28:25,302 --> 00:28:26,442
and I can't draw packets.

535
00:28:26,742 --> 00:28:30,024
Again, programmer, like these kind of things.

536
00:28:30,044 --> 00:28:32,504
So setting expectations is very important as well,

537
00:28:33,025 --> 00:28:35,045
so that when people come to you with things,

538
00:28:35,285 --> 00:28:36,746
they understand your time is valuable,

539
00:28:37,146 --> 00:28:38,927
and that when you are saying yes to something,

540
00:28:39,487 --> 00:28:42,508
that it's worth your time, it's worth their time,

541
00:28:42,548 --> 00:28:43,328
and everything is great.

542
00:28:43,869 --> 00:28:45,631
Otherwise, you'll get a little overloaded.

543
00:28:46,072 --> 00:28:47,834
So there's kind of a little bit of a balance there.

544
00:28:48,955 --> 00:28:50,678
And that's when you have to start to say no,

545
00:28:51,158 --> 00:28:53,141
because if you said yes to too many things,

546
00:28:53,542 --> 00:28:56,285
suddenly you end up in situations that aren't very good.

