00:41:04,075 --> 00:41:06,816
and sometimes we're the guest star.

802
00:41:08,557 --> 00:41:10,939
But usually, they're fun, powerful,

803
00:41:11,119 --> 00:41:12,400
and mutually beneficial.

804
00:41:15,342 --> 00:41:17,003
So what's a game industry team up?

805
00:41:17,783 --> 00:41:19,484
In the context of the game industry,

806
00:41:19,805 --> 00:41:22,066
team ups go beyond just the teams

807
00:41:22,106 --> 00:41:23,607
and the companies that you work with.

808
00:41:24,107 --> 00:41:25,708
These are the deeper relationships

809
00:41:25,788 --> 00:41:28,950
that you purposely build during your career journey.

810
00:41:30,892 --> 00:41:32,493
They're the heroes that you admire

811
00:41:32,673 --> 00:41:34,134
and the mentors that you work with.

812
00:41:35,622 --> 00:41:38,823
They're the industry peers who become confidants

813
00:41:38,903 --> 00:41:42,024
and sounding boards, resources, and friends.

814
00:41:43,405 --> 00:41:45,366
They're also the aspiring game makers

815
00:41:45,446 --> 00:41:47,807
that you take under your wing and mentor.

816
00:41:49,308 --> 00:41:52,649
So why team up?

817
00:41:52,849 --> 00:41:53,329
Three reasons.

818
00:41:54,530 --> 00:41:56,531
To develop your personal superpowers

819
00:41:56,851 --> 00:42:00,313
to get better at your job, to be more effective now

820
00:42:00,513 --> 00:42:02,494
to make better games, and then also

821
00:42:02,574 --> 00:42:04,675
to create new opportunities in the future.

822
00:42:06,390 --> 00:42:11,213
All of this can be summed up in make better games.

823
00:42:11,233 --> 00:42:13,754
Let's start with developing your personal superpowers

824
00:42:13,794 --> 00:42:16,715
by teaming up with mentors and heroes.

825
00:42:16,755 --> 00:42:19,636
You won't usually have direct access to your industry heroes,

826
00:42:20,237 --> 00:42:22,197
but you can follow them on social media.

827
00:42:22,237 --> 00:42:23,998
Following them on Twitter is a great start.

828
00:42:24,638 --> 00:42:27,660
Learning from their feed and what they talk about

829
00:42:27,720 --> 00:42:30,501
and post and retweet, this keeps you informed.

830
00:42:30,701 --> 00:42:34,383
It leaves you an opening for potential meaningful interaction.

831
00:42:36,462 --> 00:42:39,543
And then with mentors, mentors won't usually come looking for you.

832
00:42:39,703 --> 00:42:41,424
They have to be found and persuaded.

833
00:42:41,924 --> 00:42:45,425
And you have to show yourself worth the time investment

834
00:42:45,545 --> 00:42:47,565
by actually taking the advice that they give you

835
00:42:47,585 --> 00:42:51,867
and setting goals together, doing what they advise you to do.

836
00:42:54,107 --> 00:42:57,388
Mentors can help you set boundaries for work-life balance.

837
00:42:58,809 --> 00:43:00,709
They can help you navigate who you are

