00:43:28,138 --> 00:43:28,358
So,

848
00:43:30,108 --> 00:43:30,849
That's my first point.

849
00:43:31,669 --> 00:43:34,012
Choose to invest in the people that you work with now

850
00:43:34,733 --> 00:43:36,695
and choose to work with the people

851
00:43:36,735 --> 00:43:37,856
that you're already invested in.

852
00:43:41,292 --> 00:43:42,093
Trust is key.

853
00:43:43,934 --> 00:43:48,297
Making better games, I think Mary and Tara,

854
00:43:48,317 --> 00:43:50,318
a couple people touched on this already.

855
00:43:52,299 --> 00:43:56,382
Trust helps you make your games faster and better.

856
00:43:57,422 --> 00:43:59,484
Feeling like other people are invested in you

857
00:44:00,224 --> 00:44:01,705
fosters trust on your team,

858
00:44:02,265 --> 00:44:05,007
and then you're able to work more efficiently,

859
00:44:05,427 --> 00:44:06,628
uncover problems faster.

860
00:44:06,668 --> 00:44:08,589
Nobody's hiding that they're in trouble.

861
00:44:10,150 --> 00:44:11,070
or that they're behind.

862
00:44:11,810 --> 00:44:15,631
And then as you finish games and career paths diverge,

863
00:44:15,671 --> 00:44:16,732
that trust remains.

864
00:44:20,453 --> 00:44:23,634
And it's not just about efficiency

865
00:44:23,654 --> 00:44:24,754
and making great products.

866
00:44:24,834 --> 00:44:27,455
These peer team ups will also be important support

867
00:44:27,515 --> 00:44:28,775
for you during your career.

868
00:44:29,835 --> 00:44:32,256
You can't do your best work without a support network.

869
00:44:33,670 --> 00:44:36,572
These people and these relationships will cheer for your triumphs.

870
00:44:37,212 --> 00:44:40,914
They'll pull you through a world-ending layoff or studio closure.

871
00:44:40,934 --> 00:44:44,296
They'll let you vent when you really need to blow off steam.

872
00:44:45,437 --> 00:44:48,038
They'll help you figure out how to fix it when you fuck up.

873
00:44:49,439 --> 00:44:52,220
They'll encourage you to take care of yourself when you're burning out.

874
00:44:52,680 --> 00:44:54,181
And they'll remind you that you're awesome.

